{"article_id":"imqhDOr43yAKBePS","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Obamacare ' s third year of open enrollment began on Sunday .","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"People","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"hoping to sign up","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"saw a website with fresh photos and high-tech features .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"They found the actual insurance of the president ' s signature law has gotten even worse .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Unless something dramatic happens ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"this may be the year of the health care law ' s collapse .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Prices keep rising","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"and service keeps fading .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"It should not surprise the administration","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"that people are not signing up .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Despite all","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"the Obama administration has done","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"to completely upend health care in this country ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"there are still more than 30 million uninsured people in America today .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"The reason","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"they ' re not buying Obamacare","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"isn ' t because they haven ' t heard enough about it .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"They ' re not buying","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"because it ' s a bad deal for them .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"As people log on to the government exchanges this year ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"they will see the telltale signs of Obamacare ' s impending failure .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"These include :","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"costs soaring ,","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"cancellations mounting ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"and choices disappearing .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"The first thing","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"most people will notice","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"is the higher price tag .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"Premiums are jumping by double digits in many states .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"In Alaska , premiums will be nearly 40 percent higher next year .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"People","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"buying insurance on the Minnesota exchange","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"will pay anywhere from 14 to 49 percent more .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"Premiums are just one part of the high-cost story .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"Many plans are raising deductibles , co-pays , and other out-of-pocket costs .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"Remember when President Obama ' s mantra was \" If you like your health care plan ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"you can keep it ? \"","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Now the administration is singing a different tune :","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"\" If you have an Obamacare plan ,","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"you better shop around . \"","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"That ' s about the only advice","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Washington has for people","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"who want to avoid brutal rate increases .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"If you ' re willing to switch insurance plans each year ,","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"your rates may go up by slightly less .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"For some people , their old plan won ' t be available at any price .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"This includes more than a half-million people","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"insured by one of the health co-ops","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"that have shut down in 11 states over the past few months .","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"It also includes people","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"whose insurer decided","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"it simply couldn ' t afford to sell Obamacare coverage anymore .","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"That ' s what happened in my home state , Wyoming ,","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"where the company WINHealth is dropping out of the exchange entirely .","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"In some states , plans are changing dramatically","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"even if the company remains .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"A patient may find","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"that her longtime doctor will no longer be a part of her plan ' s network .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Maybe the hospital nearest to her home is no longer included by her insurance .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"These kinds of changes can leave people with very different coverage","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"than they had before .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"As people work their way around the website ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"they may notice","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"that the remaining options are slimmer than ever .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"Analysts at the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation say","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"that more of the choices will be HMOs this time around .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"That can mean narrower networks and no out-of-network coverage .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"In some states , the number of options is practically non-existent .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"According to the Kaiser Family Foundation ,","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"people","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"living in 14 of Nevada ' s 16 counties","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"will have only one or two companies","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"to pick from .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"In Wyoming , with the failure of WINHealth , residents will have only one option .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"Insurance through Obamacare is largely coming down to a simple choice","depth":5},{"id":76,"text":"of take it","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"or leave it .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"More and more Americans are leaving it .","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"The only people","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"who are consistently signing up","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"are the ones","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"who get subsidies from Washington .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"For them , the website should come with a warning label","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"reading :","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"\" Buyer beware. \"","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"According to the IRS ,","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"90 percent of people","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"who received government insurance subsidies last year","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"got the wrong amount .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"To avoid an all-out panic over low enrollment ,","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"the administration is trying to lower expectations .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"It ' s lowered the bar for success to around 10 million people enrolled for 2016 .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"That ' s half of the 21 million people","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"the non-partisan Congressional Budget Office says","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"should be covered next year .","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"It ' s also essentially flat","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"compared to the 9.9 million","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"who were enrolled in June .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"The administration is playing the lowered expectations game","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"because they know","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"how hard it is to convince more Americans to buy government-mandated insurance","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"that costs so much .","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"For so many people , Obamacare doesn ' t have much to offer .","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"Even the $ 695 tax penalty isn ' t enough incentive","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"to coerce people to buy .","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"People","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"facing premium increases along with a $ 5,000 deductible","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"see little reason","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"to pay for insurance","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"they may not want , need , or be able to afford .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"Obamacare is failing","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"because too many people want nothing","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"to do with it .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"As the costs continue to rise ,","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"more people get cancellation notices ,","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"and the exchanges offer fewer choices ,","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"the collapse will only continue .","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"We may look back at this past Sunday as the beginning of the end .","depth":4},{"id":119,"text":"- John Barrasso , chairman of the Republican Policy Committee , is a senator from Wyoming and a physician .","depth":1}],"relations":[{"parent":239,"left":238,"right":119,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":194,"right":237,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":194,"left":139,"right":193,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":139,"left":128,"right":138,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":128,"left":124,"right":127,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":124,"left":123,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":123,"left":0,"right":122,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":121,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":125,"right":126,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":138,"left":129,"right":137,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":137,"left":132,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":131,"right":14,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":131,"left":11,"right":130,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":134,"right":135,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":134,"left":133,"right":17,"relation":"sa